{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"alias":"nickelous-weedy-eagle","creation_channel":"cli","description":"Report #2: no cheap way to ask 'is this plan approved right now?' — but claim_gate_check() already computes exactly that (no LLM/network). Surface it as `rebar review-plan --status` printing certified|stale-code|stale-material|stale-regver|stale-reopened|unsigned + bound verified_at_sha, distinct exit codes, no model call. Report #6: the b3e5 idempotence short-circuit sets coverage.idempotent_skip but _render_plan_review_text shows an identical PASS with no marker — render a 'reused (cached)' line. AC: --status makes no model call; text output distinguishes a reused verdict; tests for both.","id":"9603-f939-f162-4aa7","parent_id":"29c2-19c0-2b67-47de","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Add read-only, no-LLM `review-plan --status` currency query + surface idempotent-skip in text (#2,#6)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784752648737921001,"uuid":"ced70b3e-17d2-4ca8-b713-a198d6f7bbcb"}